    "discriminators": [
     "'A hole, crack or fissure releasing gases.' The purest sustained_noise in this file: stationary, flat, smooth and long, with a low-frequency ground rumble under a broadband steam hiss.",
     "Signal-identical to AIR-HISS, WATER-STEAM and FIRE-GAS. No DSP separates a fumarole from a compressed-air leak. The weak cues are the low-frequency bed (low_band_energy well above a pneumatic hiss) and an open-air reverberant tail. Do not assert without name evidence (Fumarole, Vent, Sulphur, Geothermal, Yellowstone).",
     "Against GEYSER: a vent has no envelope. A geyser erupts — an onset ramp, a peak and a decay, so stationarity drops and spectral_flux rises."
    ],
