    "discriminators": [
     "An eruption has an ENVELOPE; a vent does not. That is the whole separation from FUMAROLE: a geyser ramps in, roars — a steam jet plus dense water-splash micro-events over a low-frequency bed — and decays. Moderate spectral_flux, mid-range stationarity, where a fumarole is flat forever.",
     "Against MUD POTS: no discrete low-frequency glops. A geyser is a continuous jet; mud pots are sparse impulses.",
     "Against WATER-TURBULENT and WATER-STEAM: the same water-and-steam physics at the same scale. Text decides (Geyser, Strokkur, Old Faithful, Yellowstone)."
    ],
