    "discriminators": [
     "A viscous low-frequency flow bed carrying sparse, irregular crackles and pops (low onset_periodicity, exactly like FIRE-CRACKLE) as the cooling crust fractures.",
     "The explanation concedes the problem itself: 'could be some overlap with FIRE, but overtly lava sounding things go here.' That is a TEXT rule, not a DSP one. Acoustically this IS FIRE-CRACKLE sitting on a rumble; the only signal cue is the extra low_band_energy and a lower spectral_centroid_hz, and it is weak.",
